Original Data
Consider a table where each row represents an attribute of a product in a retail store:

product_id	store_id	attribute_type	attribute_value
101	1	size	Large
101	1	color	Red
101	1	brand	BrandA
102	1	size	Medium
102	1	color	Blue
102	1	brand	BrandB
Pivoted Data
Pivoting this data results in a table where each product's attributes are consolidated into a single row:

product_id	store_id	size	color	brand
101	1	Large	Red	BrandA
102	1	Medium	Blue	BrandB
